.TH "Clients" "JS" "May 13, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Clients \- Clients
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is only available in Service Workers.
.PP
The \f[CR]Clients\f[R] interface provides access to \f[CR]Client\f[R]
objects.
Access it via \[ga]\f[CR]self\f[R].clients\[ga] within a service worker.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]Clients.get()\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]Promise\f[R] for a \f[CR]Client\f[R] matching a given
\f[CR]id\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]Clients.matchAll()\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]Promise\f[R] for an array of \f[CR]Client\f[R] objects.
An options argument allows you to control the types of clients returned.
.TP
\f[B]Clients.openWindow()\f[R]
Opens a new browser window for a given URL and returns a
\f[CR]Promise\f[R] for the new \f[CR]WindowClient\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]Clients.claim()\f[R]
Allows an active service worker to set itself as the
\f[CR]controller\f[R] for all clients within its \f[CR]scope\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
The following example shows an existing chat window or creates a new one
when the user clicks a notification.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]notificationclick\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  event.waitUntil(
    (\f[B]async\f[R] () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
      \f[B]const\f[R] allClients = \f[B]await\f[R] clients.matchAll({
        includeUncontrolled: \f[B]true\f[R],
      });

      \f[B]let\f[R] chatClient;

      \f[I]// Let\[aq]s see if we already have a chat window open:\f[R]
      \f[B]for\f[R] (\f[B]const\f[R] client \f[B]of\f[R] allClients) {
        \f[B]const\f[R] url = \f[B]new\f[R] URL(client.url);

        \f[B]if\f[R] (url.pathname === \[dq]/chat/\[dq]) {
          \f[I]// Excellent, let\[aq]s use it!\f[R]
          client.focus();
          chatClient = client;
          \f[B]break\f[R];
        }
      }

      \f[I]// If we didn\[aq]t find an existing chat window,\f[R]
      \f[I]// open a new one:\f[R]
      \f[B]if\f[R] (!chatClient) {
        chatClient = \f[B]await\f[R] clients.openWindow(\[dq]/chat/\[dq]);
      }

      \f[I]// Message the client:\f[R]
      chatClient.postMessage(\[dq]New chat messages!\[dq]);
    })(),
  );
});
.EE
